IRS990.MissionDescription: To promote and provide leadership in the art and science of medicine; to preserve and improve the health of all the people in Arizona by developing and maintaining the highest standards; to represent the physician and the profession in the public forum; and to defend the freedom and ability of the physician to practice medicine in the best interests of the patient.
IRS990.Description: Arizona Medical Association, Inc. (ArMA) is a non-profit corporation which serves the interest of member physicians in Arizona. In serving its members, ArMA provides the following services:1. ArMA & ArMA Annual Meeting - Meeting of the Association's members where organizational policies and procedures are discussed such as articles of incorporation and bylaws, ethics, and bio-ethics.2. Other ArMA meetings - The same as ArMA's Annual Meeting above except held twice a year with delegates of the Association's members sent to discuss issues affecting medicine and the community.3. Involvement in Governmental Affairs - Legislative committees, lobbyists, and assistants organized for the primary purpose of influencing federal and state legislation in the interest of organized medicine.4. Public relations and publications - Production of "Arizona Medicine," a monthly journal to members informing the membership of current legislative and business issues affecting both the membership and the community.5. Seminars, workshops, and CME Program6. Specialty services and accounting to specialty societies7. MD Record - A Software program designed to assist physicians with the credentialing process8. Doctor's Day Q&A - Television program coordinated with Blue Cross Channel 3 and MAS AZ

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.ReturnReference: Description of Uncertain Tax Positions Under FIN 48:
Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: The Organization has adopted the provisions of FASB Accounting Standards Codification Topic ASC 740-10 (previously Financial Interpretation No. 48, Accounting for Uncertainty in Income Taxes), on June 1, 2009. The implementation of this standard had no impact on the combined financial statements. As of both the date of adoption, and as of June 30, 2010, the unrecognized tax benefit accrual was zero. The Organization will recognize future accrued interest and penalties related to unrecognized tax benefits in income tax expense if incurred. The Organization is no longer subject to Federal examinations by tax authorities for years before 2006 and state examinations for years before 2005.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 6
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The organization has members in the following classes: Active, Fifty-Year Club, Associate, Service, Affiliate, and Honorary. All classes have similar duties and privileges, except Associate and Honorary members may not serve as delegates or hold any elective or appointive office.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 7a
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The organization's House of Delegates elects the members of the Board of Directors. Each delegate is entitled to one vote, provided that they are members of Arizona Medical Association, Inc.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The organization's signing officer reviews the return before filing.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: A conflict of interest form is distributed annually to all officers, directors, and key employees. If a conflict exists, the board member is expected to disclose the conflict to the Board of Directors. A board member with a conflict is restricted from voting on related matters.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15a
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Executive Committee reviews and approves the top management official's compensation annually after considering data related to comparable positions at other trade associations. This process was last undertaken in the current year.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19

GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The process has not changed from the prior year.

Chic Older and David Landrith, Executive Vice President and Vice President of Public Policy, respectively, each dedicate 1 hour per week to Arizona Medical Association Foundation, a related organization. All other board members also dedicate 1 hour per week to Arizona Medical Association Foundation.
